Secret Super Way to Learn Anything Quickly #humor'], ['Cheburashka who is looking for friends.Yesterday, at the mentoring session, we analyzed a request for a search for a business partner. A classic case: a techie came up with "how to change the world", tried to implement it, but realized (and this is already half the way to overcome the obstacle) that he lacks competence in economics and sales.One of the experts recommended looking for a business partner. Question: how to find such a person?To begin with, I would recommend thinking about whether there is enough space for two in your business? If it\'s a boutique idea, not scalable, where you can only work as a self-employed person, then looking for a partner will not be the most effective strategy. In this case, I recommend that you first work out your attitude towards this business with a coach (why do I want to pursue this idea, what is the real reason). To understand whether the scale of implementation suits me, whether the idea itself is important to me, and what needs I cover for myself. At this moment, the understanding often comes that the point is not in the idea, but in satisfying the need for recognition, fame, etc. Determine the scale of recognition required (first guy in the village or Nobel laureate) and dig your idea again. Try to "fry" your dreams on the accelerator (fortunately there are a lot of them now), when the format of the event itself motivates you to twist your idea from different angles. By the way, at the accelerator, many startups decide that the implementation is pointless, but even more founders change the product and areas of application of their technology.See how much preparatory work needs to be done "with oneself", and we have not yet reached the partnership at all. If, after all these actions, you are still sure that you need a partner, and not a hired "salesman", only then go "on the warpath".A possible source is your environment (friends, communities). The accelerators release founders and team members who have become disillusioned with the idea and who may well strengthen your team. I observe such partnership at almost all accelerators, the main thing is not to be afraid to immediately declare this goal so that other participants know that they can join you.The very first thing you should pay attention to when evaluating a partnership opportunity is similar values. Not similar strengths and weaknesses (on the contrary, you should complement each other), namely values, your picture of the world, boundaries and attitudes. Just talk to each other, find out about hobbies, how and who spends their free time, what they like and what infuriates, etc. Treat the conversation not as an evaluation interview, but as a mutual acquaintance, not only do you "buy", but you are "buyed".Here are some simple tips, but a very difficult way... How late are you getting this information?'], ['A magical way to drastically increase conversionsDiscussing yesterday\'s post about customer segmentation, we touched upon an important point in understanding the client\'s portrait, his pains and proposed solutions. It is foolish to assume that yesterday\'s graduate and experienced specialist will buy an educational course for the same reasons. So why do we so often drive traffic from different segments to the same page?A potential client, visiting the page, should receive unambiguous and clear answers to their 5 why\'s:1. Why is this about me?2. Why is this my problem? Do I really have it?3. Why, what you suggest will solve my problem? And decide exactly?4. Why should I buy from you, why not look at others?5. After all, he "just keeps a diary of training."If you go to the gym occasionally (sometimes you understand that you need to take new levels in business), then a trainer (tracker) is hired in order to identify the biggest problems, make an audit, and determine the sequence of training. All these points came together - the idea was to create a meetup that would immerse the audience in analytics without overloading them with technical details.‚ñ´Ô∏èWhat was the topic of the meetup and why?I decided that the meetup would consist of two parts - a basic report "Product analytics - where to start?" and a workshop on metrics, A/B testing, and product cases.\xa0- Why not tell companies in Moldova how to build analytics and what it can do for them? Here I wanted to give some thoughts on how to implement analytics in a company.\xa0- The second part of the meetup is a bit more complicated - there were ideas to talk about some of our product cases, but then I would have to do it myself. Two reports in a row from one speaker could be boring, so I decided to hold a workshop with my analyst colleague. During the workshop, we planned to divide the audience into several groups and let them solve small product analysis cases for 5-10 minutes each.\xa0\xa0‚ñ´Ô∏èHow did I prepare for the meetup? - Public speaking lessonsAt the beginning of 2022, I took some classes in rhetoric and public speaking, learned to breathe properly, speak clearly, etc.\xa0Now I decided to take some more lessons to rehearse the presentation. We discussed how to present the information, what to emphasize, and when to pause. In general, there was a necessary foundation. - Training with a mentorIt is necessary to give only verified information in order not to mislead people, right?\xa0To make sure the information is correct throughout the meeting, I called my mentor. He can point out mistakes, advise on something more complete or even bring in new ideas. Also, when there is no opportunity to give a presentation in a company or elsewhere, such advice is very useful. ‚ñ´Ô∏èWhat this meetup will do:- Develop my personal brand\xa0- Increase my company\'s brand awareness- The first public speaking experience for me and my colleagueDo you have any experience in public speaking?', '30'], ["Last week I was delighted to initiate and speak at a Product Analytics Meetup and Workshop in Moldova!I'll tell you more about the preparations soon :)", '4'], ["Decided it was time to share my experience with my younger colleagues! I‚Äôll be a mentor in the next Women In Tech program (https://women-in-tech.org). Applied about a month ago, and recently found out I passed! üí´The program takes place approximately every 6 months. You can become either a mentee or a mentor, but in both cases you need to be pre-screened. Both men and women can be mentors, however, only women can be mentees.
